To set up this project locally, follow these steps:

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/casecrafted/casecrafted.git
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd casecrafted
Install Jekyll:

If you don't already have Jekyll installed, follow the Jekyll installation guide for your system.

Run the local development server:

bash
Copy code
bundle exec jekyll serve
Open the project:

Once the server is running, open a web browser and go to:

bash
Copy code
http://localhost:4000/casecrafted/
Usage
This website uses Jekyll and GitHub Pages for static site generation and hosting. Below are some key usage instructions:

How to Add New Products
Add product images to the assets/images folder.
Exclude logo.png from the images folder (this is done automatically in the code).
The products page will dynamically display all images except for logo.png.
Folder Structure
The project follows a well-structured hierarchy:

bash
Copy code
casecrafted/
├── _config.yml               # Jekyll configuration file
├── _posts/                   # Blog posts (if applicable)
├── _layouts/                 # HTML layouts for pages
│   ├── default.html          # Default layout for all pages
│   ├── home.html             # Layout for the home page
├── _includes/                # Reusable HTML components
│   ├── header.html           # Header section
│   ├── footer.html           # Footer section
├── assets/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css        # Main stylesheet for the site
│   └── images/               # Images for products and logos
├── index.html                # Home page
├── about.html                # About page
├── products.html             # Products page
├── contact.html              # Contact page
├── README.md                 # Project documentation (this file)
└── CNAME                     # Custom domain configuration (optional)
Technologies Used
Jekyll: Static site generator used for building the site.
GitHub Pages: Hosting platform for the site.
HTML/CSS: For structuring and styling the website.
Liquid: Templating engine used within Jekyll for dynamic content generation.
